The paper discusses progress in the field of AI algorithms for prediction, search, inductive inference, problem solving, decision making, and reinforcement learning in environments of a very general type. These topics are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.DS, and cs.SE. Additionally, the paper mentions the relevance of the results for physics, which could also suggest a potential fit for the cs.PH sub-category. However, given the focus on AI algorithms, the other sub-categories are more likely.
